        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-16 17:34:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nCan we get the ci-management jobs set up so we get a verify?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "01a58135fcd7716c97e2b0ecbf5ec619755511fe",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 75,
          "name": "Venkata Harish Kajur",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vk250x@att.com",
          "username": "vk250x"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-17 17:21:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@Pavel, your code relies on the xsd? Schema service doesn't return the xsd, it returns the oxm file. Will your code be able to handle oxm files?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "3b60b531d00ee3693cad804d407733f2b79250e7",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-18 00:52:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@harish other AAI clients will still be using XSD until well after schema-service is established. won't there still be some method for getting the XSD that matches the OXM?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "fde1c5ebe846810edcfc7eb8c64321d8886e5887",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2381,
          "name": "Pavel Paroulek",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pavel.paroulek@orange.com",
          "username": "wageslave"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-18 14:38:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@Harish - the code does not expect xsd nor oxm. The file \"aai_schema_v11.xsd\" is used only to read vertex names for testing purposes only. Currently there is NO data provider except dummy vertices read from the xsd and random edges between them. \n\nAs to what format will GraphGraph use as input depends on the Schema-Service API, once the API is revealed to the community a decision is going to be made on the exact API calls to get data from the Schema-Service.\n\n@Jimmy - how can this be set up? What does it check?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "90f107dab7c1c6b1dda5e0771d10f558e2112249",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 75,
          "name": "Venkata Harish Kajur",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vk250x@att.com",
          "username": "vk250x"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-18 18:36:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@Keong, the method for getting the xsd will still be similar to how it was before in the jar. I was worried that the assumption that the schema service will provide rest endpoints to retrieve the xsd. It seems like that's not the case.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "1b226e8e19db24882399b697578c4b46b57b60d9",
        "author": {
